§ 151.085 CC-CD COMMERCIAL CORRIDOR CONDITIONAL DISTRICT.
A. Generally. The Commercial Corridor Conditional District establishes minimum required standards to accomplish high
quality, low impact, community-oriented mixed retail and office type developments in designated areas along Rea Road
and NC 16. Commercial developments must be designed SO the combination of uses proposed, pose relatively little
impact on surrounding neighborhoods and local streets. Structures must be built using high-quality building materials
along with superior architectural design features and exterior finishes. Rezoning CC-CD shall only be permitted in areas
SO designated for future retail/office development on the Village Land Use Plan. Commercial developments may only
occur in conjunction with an application for a Conditional District as outlined in § 151.251.
B. Applicability.
1. Commercial Corridor development applications will only be considered when all fees and all submittal requirements
are provided, in accordance with requirements for a petition to a Conditional Zoning District and the regulations
outlined in this section. A CC-CD application and petition for conditional rezoning must adhere to all applicable sub-
district ordinances.
2. A rezoning to the Commercial Corridor Conditional District shall require the submittal of a detailed application and a
plan, in accordance with § 151.251; illustrating uses, setbacks, architectural design elements, open space, active and
passive recreational opportunities, landscaping, screening and buffering, parking and vehicular circulation, signage
and tree preservation. The proposed details shall be consistent with the goals and objectives of the Land Use Plan, the
Zoning Ordinance, the tree ordinance and all other plans adopted by the village.
3. Approval of a Commercial Corridor Conditional District rezoning may constitute a sketch plan approval as described
in § 151.251(A)(3).
