D. Development standards.
1. Setbacks.
a. The setbacks for buildings and structures within the district are as follows:
1. The minimum building setback shall be 85 feet from any major or minor road or any major or minor
thoroughfare.
2. The minimum building setback from the property line of a residentially zoned property shall be 100 feet.
3. The minimum building setback shall be 25 feet from all other property lines which are not part of the
development.
b. Where a public road right-of-way along a major or minor thoroughfare has not been established by the North
Carolina Department of Transportation, the right-of-way shall be determined by a measurement of 50 feet from the
centerline of the pavement to the measured line to provide for future widening.
C.
Only passive recreation facilities (benches, fountains, gazebos and the like) shall be allowed within required
setbacks.
2. Landscaping.
a. Commercial landscaping.
1. Landscaping, screening, buffers, berms, tree preservation and mitigation shall meet or exceed the minimum
standards per § 151.046 and the most recently adopted village tree ordinance, as codified in CHAPTER 93 of this
Code of Ordinances.
2. All such landscaping, screening, buffers and berms of planted and existing trees, shrubs and other vegetation
shall include, protect, and maintain existing and planted trees within the tree preservation strips and areas in
compliance with the most recently adopted version of the Marvin tree ordinance, as codified in CHAPTER 93 of
this Code of Ordinances.
